1. What is a Router?

        English: A router is a network device that connects different networks together and decides the best path for data to travel.
        
        Hindi: Router ek aisa device hai jo alag-alag networks ko jodta hai aur data packet ko bhejne ke liye best rasta choose karta hai.

ğŸ‘‰ Switch = ek hi network ke andar devices connect karta hai.
ğŸ‘‰ Router = alag networks ko connect karta hai.

2. Why Router is Important?

        Without routers, your LAN (ghar/office network) canâ€™t talk to another LAN (like your friendâ€™s home or Googleâ€™s servers).
        
        Jaise tumhare ghar ka WiFi Router tumhara local network (phone/laptop) ko Internet (world network) se jodta hai.

3. What is Router IOS?

        IOS = Internetwork Operating System
        
        Ye ek software hai jo router ke andar chalta hai.
        
        Isi ke through hum configure karte hain router ko (via CLI commands).
        
        Example: ip route, show running-config etc.

ğŸ‘‰ Hindi: Router ek box hai, aur IOS uska dimaag (brain) hai.
Without IOS, router ek khaali dabba hai.

4. Functions of a Router

        Packet Forwarding â†’ data ko best path se bhejna.
        
        Path Selection â†’ routing protocols use karke best route decide karna.
        
        Internetworking â†’ alag networks (LANâ€“WANâ€“Internet) ko connect karna.
        
        Security â†’ ACLs, firewall rules apply karna.
        
        Addressing â†’ IP addresses ko samajhna aur unke basis pe decision lena.

5. Router Interfaces

        LAN Interface (Ethernet/FastEthernet/Gigabit) â†’ local network connect karne ke liye.
        
        WAN Interface (Serial, Fiber, DSL) â†’ Internet ya dusre remote network ke liye.

